  "prompt": "Where can I learn Hadoop online for free?",
  "response": "Learning Hadoop online for free is definitely possible through various platforms that offer quality educational content. Here are some options where you can find free courses and tutorials on Hadoop:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many educators and professionals upload detailed video tutorials on Hadoop. Channels like \"Edureka\", \"Simplilearn\", \"Coursera\", and \"freeCodeCamp.org\" often have comprehensive playlists on Hadoop.\n\n2. **Coursera**: While many courses on Coursera are paid, they also offer financial aid and free audit options for many of their courses. You can search for Hadoop courses and audit them for free.\n\n3. **edX**: Similar to Coursera, edX offers free courses with the option to pay for certifications. You can find Hadoop courses provided by universities and institutions that you can audit for free.\n\n4. **Udemy**: Udemy often has sales where many courses become very affordable, and sometimes even free. Keep an eye out for such deals by regularly visiting the website.\n\n5. **Codecademy**: While Codecademy primarily focuses on coding, they offer some free courses and learner plans, though their in-depth Hadoop courses may require a subscription.\n\n6. **LinkedIn Learning**: You can access LinkedIn Learning (formerly Lynda.com) for free through various public libraries or academic institutions that offer it to their members or students.\n\n7. **GitHub**: Many developers share free resources, tutorials, and course materials on their GitHub repositories. It's a great place for more hands-on, code-based learning.\n\n8. **FreeCodeCamp**: This platform offers extensive free content on many programming topics, and while it may not have a dedicated Hadoop course, it does have associated technology courses (like Big Data).\n\n9. **IBM Developer**: Offers free tutorials, articles, and courses on Hadoop and related technologies.\n\n10. **Khan Academy**: Though primarily focused on math and science, they sometimes offer courses and tutorials related to computer science and data.\n\nMake sure to also check educational blogs, forums, and official documentation which can be extremely helpful in addition to structured courses. Happy learning!",
